## Kibana Rule Configuration

### Create Detection Rule via API

```bash
curl -X POST "localhost:9200/.kibana/_doc/_create" \
-H 'kbn-xsrf: true' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d'{
  "name": "Office Application Spawning Shell Interpreter",
  "type": "query",
  "enabled": true,
  "risk_score": 75,
  "severity": "high",
  "rule_type": "query",
  "query": "process.parent.name : (\"winword.exe\" OR \"excel.exe\" OR \"powerpnt.exe\") AND process.name : (\"powershell.exe\" OR \"cmd.exe\" OR \"wscript.exe\")",
  "index": ["logs-endpoint.events-*"],
  "interval": "5m",
  "from": "now-30m"
}'
```

### Detection Rule Configuration

```json
{
  "rule": {
    "name": "T1566.001 - Office Application Spawning Shell",
    "description": "Detects office applications spawning command interpreters indicating macro execution",
    "query": "process.parent.name : (\"winword.exe\" OR \"excel.exe\" OR \"powerpnt.exe\") AND process.name : (\"powershell.exe\" OR \"cmd.exe\" OR \"wscript.exe\")",
    "risk_score": 75,
    "severity": "high",
    "rule_type": "threat_match",
    "interval": "5m",
    "from": "now-30m",
    "actions": [
      {
        "type": "slack",
        "notification_action_type_id": "slack",
        "channel": "#security-alerts",
        "message": "Office application spawning shell interpreter detected on {{host.name}}"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

