## Advanced Hunting Queries

### Correlate Multiple Detections in Kill Chain

```kusto
index: logs-endpoint.events-* 
(
  (process.parent.name : ("winword.exe" OR "excel.exe") AND process.name : "powershell.exe")
  OR (process.name : "powershell.exe" AND process.command_line : "-EncodedCommand")
  OR (process.command_line : ("sekurlsa::logonpasswords" OR "-ma lsass"))
)
| stats count() as event_count, values(event.action) as actions, values(timestamp) as times
  by host.name, user.name
| where event_count >= 2
```

### Hunt for Registry Persistence + Credential Dumping

```kusto
index: logs-endpoint.events-* 
(registry.key : "*Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*" AND event.action : "RegistryValueSet")
OR (process.command_line : "sekurlsa::logonpasswords")
| stats count() as event_count, min(timestamp) as first_activity, max(timestamp) as last_activity
  by host.name, user.name
| where event_count >= 2
```

### Network Exfiltration Pattern Detection

```kusto
index: logs-endpoint.events-* 
(process.name : ("curl.exe" OR "wget.exe" OR "ftp.exe") AND process.command_line : ("http://" OR "https://"))
AND destination.domain : ("*.ru" OR "*.ir" OR "*.gq" OR "*.tk")
| stats count() as connection_count, values(destination.domain) as domains
  by host.name, user.name, process.command_line
```

